text:
Once upon a time there was an old mother pig who had one hundred little pigs and not enough food to feed them. So when they were old enough, she sent them out into the world to seek their fortunes. You know the story about the first three little pigs. This is a story about the 92nd little pig.

The 92nd little pig built a house out of depleted uranium. And the wolf was like, "dude." The 92nd little pig was like, "what?" The wolf said, "Can I come in?" The 92nd little pig replied, "No." And the wolf asked, "Why not?" The 92nd little pig said, "Because you're a wolf." But the wolf vowed, "I'm not a wolf, I'm a sheep in wolf's clothing." The 92nd little pig said, "If you're a sheep in wolf's clothing, then I'm a wolf in sheep's clothing." The wolf was like, "You're not a wolf in sheep's clothing, you're a pig." The 92nd little pig said, "I'm not a pig, I'm a wolf." And the wolf reiterated, "I'm not a wolf, I'm a sheep." The 92nd little pig insisted, "If you're a sheep, then I'm a wolf." The wolf then lost patience. He said, "I'm a wolf, and I'm coming in." The 92nd little pig felt scared and helpless. All out of a sudden, the old mother pig and the other 99 little pigs came running up. They said, "We're here to help you." All the pigs stepped onto the wolf. The wolf was like, "Ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow, ow.
